Maurice Ave., north side, at 65th Street, showing a frame house at the N.W. corner. In the background appears that area between Queens Boulevard (right) and Mt. Zion Cemetery (left) with the Woodside Brewery prominent on the horizon. At the left is the Thomas H. Betts farmhouse of 1852 (clothesline suspended therefrom).

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

A general view northwest from Maurice Ave. and 65th Street, showing the area between Queens Boulevard (right) and Mt. Zion Cemetery (left). Prominently shown on the horizon is the Woodside Brewery. To the left of same and near the seam in this composite view is the Thomas H. Betts farm house of 1852 (clothesline suspended therefrom) which was later known as the Erb's homestead. In the foreground are houses at the N.W. corner of the aforementioned point.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
